'''McPherson Unit''' is a [[Incarceration of women|prison for women]] of the [[Arkansas Department of Correction]], located in [[Newport, Arkansas|Newport]], [[Arkansas]], off of [[Arkansas Highway 384]], {{convert|4|mi|km}} east of central Newport. Established in 1998,<ref>"[http://www.adc.arkansas.gov/facilities/facilities3.html#mcpherson McPherson Unit]." [[Arkansas Department of Correction]]. Retrieved on November 22, 2010.</ref> the prison houses the state's death row for women.<ref name="Haddigan">Haddigan, Michael. "[http://web.archive.org/web/19990508130907/http://www.arktimes.com/990409coverstory.html They Kill Women, Don't They?]" ''[[Arkansas Times]]''. April 9, 1999. Retrieved on August 15, 2010.</ref>

The unit houses a campus of the Riverside Vocational Technical School.<ref>"[http://www.riversidevtech.org/gpage.html Campuses]." Riverside Vocational Technical School. Retrieved on March 6, 2011.</ref>

Originally it was managed by the Wackenhut Corrections Corp. (now [[GEO Group]]), with the management contract beginning in July 1997. In 2001, after operating the McPherson Unit and the nearby [[Grimes Unit]] at losses, Wackenhut stated that it would not renew the contract.<ref>"[http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=MH&s_site=miami&p_multi=MH&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB72FEA079B9441&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM WACKENHUT TO GET OUT OF PRISON CONTRACTS]." ''[[Miami Herald]]''. February 17, 2001. 1C Business. Retrieved on March 7, 2011.</ref>

==Notable prisoners==
Death row
* Christina Marie Riggs- Executed May 2, 2000

